Happy Sunday!

Tomorrow is the first day of school at STEAM Academy of Warren. I want to welcome you to the 2020-2021 school year. It is an honor to serve your children this year and I take their safety as my number one priority. To that end, please follow the following school policies.

1. Students can begin entering the building at 9:00 am. Breakfast will be from 9:00 am - 9:25 am. Dismissal will be at 4:00 PM. During the Pandemic, only ACCEL Employees and contractors will be allowed in the building during school hours. This is to protect our students and staff.

post_text:
Hello, this is Jon Natko, Head of School at STEAM Academy. As all of you know, school will start on Monday. I am looking forward to seeing smiling faces and for the opportunity to work with many of you online. If you have signed up for Hybrid or Online and have not picked up your computer, you can come between 1-3 today or 1-3 tomorrow to the gym to pick up the computers. If you need busing, you need to go to the Warren City Schools website, then go to departments and hit business and then transportation. There will be an online form for community school transportation and you will out that form.

There will an online meet the teacher day for all Hybrid and Online students on Thursday from 2:15 - 3:00 pm. We will email you the link. If we do not have a current email, please get it to us ASAP. Please continue to update your phone numbers throughout the year. We have an active Facebook page and website. Please check both sites throughout the year for information. Have a great day!

Steam Academy Families: This month the state of Ohio is requiring a new proof of residency to be submitted. You can earn a $5.00 gift card for completing this task!

Ways to turn in a new proof of residency:

1) Text a picture of a new POR to 216.208.5052
2) Bring a new POR to school during lunch pick up
3) Send in a picture of a new POR on Class DOJO
4) Email a picture of a new POR admissions@accelschools.com

Submit a new proof of residency by 5/12/20 and receive a $5 shopping gift card, per family.

*Please note that without an updated proof of residency, Warren City will not grant bus services for the 2020-2021 school year and state funding will stop.*

post_text:
We borrowed today's craft from another STEAM family! Let's put those toilet paper rolls to use and make paper tube flowers! If you decide to do this craft please take pictures and share them on this post.

Step 1: paint or color the stem, leaves, and stigma parts of the flower.

Step 2: take your paper tube and paint or color whatever color you want the petals to be.

Step 3: cut the paper tube into 6-7 pieces.

Step 4: glue your petals on the flower

Step 5: add anything else to the BACKGROUND.

Can’t wait to see your flowers. Enjoy!

Step 2: take your paper tube and paint or color whatever color you want the petals to be.

Starting April 20th, teachers will be available, at a set time, every school day so that students can log into a platform called Canvas and can receive help with their lessons. Parents will get information of how to get on Canvas shortly.… More

post_text:
As most of you are aware, Ohio Governor Mike DeWine has extended the school closure until May 1. As always our main concern is that all students and families remain safe during this time. With that in mind we have made the decision to mail all printed learning resources home weekly for our students to continue their learning during this time. If your address has changed since we were last in school, please call the office and leave a message with your new address so we can ensure all materials make it to our students. Further information will be sent home about returning these learning resources. As always everyone’s safety is our main concern and we will keep you up-to-date as soon as we know more.

Please be on the lookout next week for some fun activities we will be posting daily and videos from our staff members!

post_text: Good morning families, we are continuing to monitor the coronavirus situation and make adjustments in the best interest of student and staff safety. To help prevent the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19), we are cancelling all scheduled field trips and prohibiting spectator participation at extra-curricular events. If you have specific questions about an event, feel free to call the school or email the front office. Thank you for your understanding. We will continue to post updates as they come.
